son` field in its JSON responses (to save tokens), but JavaScript was still trying to display it, showing "💡 undefined".

## The Fix

Added proper checks to only show fields when they have actual values:
- `reason` field: Only shows if it exists AND isn't the string "undefined"
- `location` field: Only shows if it exists AND has a name property

